  "zipball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/DataDog/datadog-lambda-js/zipball/v12.141.0",
  "body": ">[!IMPORTANT]\r\n> Datadog APM now supports AWS Lambda Durable Functions. To maintain retention consistency for spans across a long-running durable execution, **create a retention filter with the retention query `operation_name:aws.durable.execute`**. Note that standard trace retention limits still apply.\r\n>\r\n> By default, the tracer creates additional checkpoints named `_datadog_{N}` to propagate trace context across function invocations. This keeps spans from multiple invocations in a single intact trace for each durable execution. To disable this behavior and treat each invocation as an individual trace, set the environment variable `DD_DURABLE_CROSS_INVOCATION_TRACING_ENABLED` to `false`.\r\n\r\n\r\n>[!IMPORTANT]\r\n> This version imports `dd-trace-js` [v5.114.0](https://github.com/DataDog/dd-trace-js/releases/tag/v5.114.0)\r\n\r\nFull Changelogs:\r\n- dd-trace https://github.com/DataDog/dd-trace-js/compare/v5.109.0...v5.114.0\r\n- datadog-lambda-js https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-js/compare/v12.140.0...v12.141.0\r\n\r\n## What's Changed\r\n* chore(engines): add ignore-engines flag by @pabloerhard in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-js/pull/793\r\n* v12.141.0 by @joeyzhao2018 in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-js/pull/796\r\n* fix(deps): vuln minor upgrades — 14 packages (minor: 6 · patch: 8)  by @gh-worker-campaigns-3e9aa4[bot] in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-js/pull/794\r\n* fix(deps): vuln axios (minor → 1.18.1) [integration_tests] by @gh-worker-campaigns-3e9aa4[bot] in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-js/pull/795\r\n* chore: upgrade dd-trace to v5.114.0 by @joeyzhao2018 in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-js/pull/797\r\n\r\n## New Contributors\r\n* @pabloerhard made their first contribution in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-js/pull/793\r\n* @gh-worker-campaigns-3e9aa4[bot] made their first contribution in https://github.com/DataDog/datadog-lambda-js/pull/794\r\n\r\n\r\n```yml\r\n# AWS Commercial\r\narn:aws:lambda:<AWS_REGION>:464622532012:layer:Datadog-Node18-x:141\r\narn:aws:lambda:<AWS_REGION>:464622532012:layer:Datadog-Node20-x:141\r\narn:aws:lambda:<AWS_REGION>:464622532012:layer:Datadog-Node22-x:141\r\narn:aws:lambda:<AWS_REGION>:464622532012:layer:Datadog-Node24-x:141\r\n\r\n# AWS GovCloud\r\narn:aws-us-gov:lambda:us-gov-<AWS_REGION>:<ACCOUNT>:layer:Datadog-Node18-x:141\r\narn:aws-us-gov:lambda:us-gov-<AWS_REGION>:<ACCOUNT>:layer:Datadog-Node20-x:141\r\narn:aws-us-gov:lambda:us-gov-<AWS_REGION>:<ACCOUNT>:layer:Datadog-Node22-x:141\r\narn:aws-us-gov:lambda:us-gov-<AWS_REGION>:<ACCOUNT>:layer:Datadog-Node24-x:141\r\n\r\nACCOUNT =\r\n002406178527 for us1 environment\r\n486696501492 for us2 environment\r\n```\r\n",
